news.headline: Earnings live: Tesla stock falls after earnings miss, IBM sinks
news.summary: The third quarter of 2014 is expected to be the best for the U.S. economy since 2009. The economy is set to grow by 0.4% this year.
news.article_text:
Earnings season is ramping up as Tesla (TSLA), Netflix (NFLX), General Motors (GM), and Ford Motor Company (F), among others, report results this week.

As of Oct. 17, 12% of S&P 500 companies have reported results, according to FactSet data, and analysts are expecting an 8.5% jump in earnings per share during the third quarter. If that figure holds, it would mark the ninth straight quarter of positive earnings growth but a deceleration from the 12% earnings growth reported in Q2 of this year.

Tutor Perini (TPC) closed the most recent trading day at $64.22, moving -3.96% from the previous trading session. The stock trailed the S&P 500, which registered a daily loss of 0.53%. Meanwhile, the Dow lost 0.71%, and the Nasdaq, a tech-heavy index, lost 0.93%.

news.headline: Crown Castle raises annual site rental revenue forecast on robust demand
news.summary: Crown Castle raised its annual site rental revenue forecast for the second time. The real estate investment trust derives majority of its revenue from leasing out tower infrastructure to U.S. wireless carriers.
news.article_text:
(Reuters) -Wireless tower operator Crown Castle on Wednesday raised its annual site rental revenue forecast for the second time, helped by steady demand for wireless infrastructure services.

Crown Castle derives majority of its revenue from leasing out tower infrastructure to U.S. wireless carriers such as AT&T, T-Mobile US, and Verizon Communications on a long-term basis.
